"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-sport-sport-olympics-olympics-2024-tom-pidcock-gold-b1173546.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 56, \"end\": 76, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Google Custom Search\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search.\", \"from\": 125, \"to\": 182, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"See our privacy policy for more information.\", \"from\": 183, \"to\": 227, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sport|Olympics  Tom Pidcockstormed back from a front puncture to take a second consecutive Olympic mountain bike gold in dramatic fashion at the Paris Games.\", \"from\": 229, \"to\": 386, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Pidcock's race was in danger of unravelling when he suffered a flat front tyre on the fourth of eight laps, shortly after he had taken control of the 35km race with an attack which split the pack.\", \"from\": 388, \"to\": 584, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Having fallen 40 seconds behind French hope Victor Koretzky, Pidcock fought his way back to reclaim the lead with a lap and a half to go, but the pair traded blows in the last couple of kilometres - dramatically touching wheels - before Pidcock burst forward to take the win.\", \"from\": 586, \"to\": 861, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 618, \"end\": 624, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.48093962600007856, \"rank\": 0.6837114205462054, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 630, \"end\": 645, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Koretzky\", \"score\": 0.9999880939516794, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Victor Koretzky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Koretzky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Koretzky\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Pidcock was booed by the home crowds at Elancourt Hill, who had been ecstatic when Koretzky had attacked on the final climb of the race - the sort of territory where Pidcock would be expected to make a move - to take the lead late on.\", \"from\": 863, \"to\": 1097, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 903, \"end\": 912, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9lancourt\", \"score\": 0.9999999999663487, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Elancourt\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9lancourt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9lancourt\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But their hearts would be broken after Pidcock got his nose in front of Koretzky as the path narrowed before a tree, the decisive moment in a tense race.\", \"from\": 1099, \"to\": 1252, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After a relatively poor start, Pidcock had moved to the front on the third lap and then took control, only for things to unravel with a front flat tyre.\", \"from\": 1254, \"to\": 1406, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Aquatics GB 'immensely disappointed' as Proud joins Enhanced Games  Sports quiz of 2024: 100 hard questions on an incredible year  Keely Hodgkinson reveals Grand Slam Track decision and 2025 ambitions  Discover a hidden island paradise in the Indian Ocean  Pidcock was lucky in that it happened close to the pits but his team were not ready for him and it was a slow change, leading Pidcock down in ninth place, the gap to the front suddenly ballooning.\", \"from\": 1408, \"to\": 1861, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1539, \"end\": 1555, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Keely Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He caught back up to catch Koretzky with two laps to go, but the effort told as he could not shake off the Frenchman until the very last.\", \"from\": 1863, \"to\": 2000, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is only 16 days since Pidcock pulled out of the Tour de France suffering from Covid.\", \"from\": 2002, \"to\": 2089, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The reigning mountain bike world champion had made this race his number one target all season, and his determination to deliver showed in the final two laps of a pulsating contest.\", \"from\": 2091, \"to\": 2271, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Pidcock revealed how his racing instincts had got him over the line for gold.\", \"from\": 2273, \"to\": 2350, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was all going pretty well and I knew that Victor would be strong and then the puncture happened.\", \"from\": 2352, \"to\": 2452, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2398, \"end\": 2404, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Newman\", \"score\": 0.9990346719695423, \"rank\": 0.0009643477194856848, \"text\": \"Victor\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Newman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Newman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We were not ready in the pits but he did a fast change and I knew at that point that I had five laps and thought anything was possible.\", \"from\": 2453, \"to\": 2588, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Suddenly I was coming really fast back to Victor but I could not get rid of him and I knew how fast he was on the last lap.\", \"from\": 2590, \"to\": 2714, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2633, \"end\": 2639, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Newman\", \"score\": 0.9990346719695423, \"rank\": 0.0009643477194856848, \"text\": \"Victor\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Newman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Newman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the end, I just had to go for a gap.\", \"from\": 2715, \"to\": 2754, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Racing is what I have always done and the Olympics is not different.\", \"from\": 2755, \"to\": 2823, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am sorry for him, the support for him was incredible but it's the Olympics so you have got to go all in.\", \"from\": 2825, \"to\": 2932, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics is so special and you need to never give up.\", \"from\": 2933, \"to\": 2990, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"In the lead up the Olympics so many things run through your head.\", \"from\": 2992, \"to\": 3058, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Emotions, scenarios, and, by the time you get on the startline, you are a bit knackered as it is.\", \"from\": 3059, \"to\": 3156, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I can not thank everyone enough.\", \"from\": 3158, \"to\": 3191, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Everyone around me has helped me train perfectly.\\\"\", \"from\": 3192, \"to\": 3242, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"MORE ABOUT  Have your say...  1  Crime  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line train after youths told to stop vaping by middle-aged passenger  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line after youths told to stop vaping  2  Football  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup, confirmed team news, injury latest for Premier League today  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup and confirmed team news  3  UK  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning over Donald Trump's Iran war  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning on Iran war  4  Lifestyle  Horosco